{"comments":"Tilt Atoms — Bounded numeric parameters for pen tilt dynamics.\n\n## Design Philosophy\n\nTilt describes the angle of a stylus relative to the drawing surface.\nTwo coordinate systems are supported:\n\n1. **Cartesian (TiltX, TiltY)**: Decomposed horizontal/vertical tilt\n2. **Polar (Altitude, Azimuth)**: Angle from surface + direction\n\nMost hardware reports Cartesian; polar is often more intuitive for\nbrush behavior (altitude = how flat, azimuth = which direction).\n\n## Key Properties\n\n- **TiltX**: Horizontal tilt angle (-90 to 90 degrees, clamps)\n- **TiltY**: Vertical tilt angle (-90 to 90 degrees, clamps)\n- **Altitude**: Angle from surface (0=flat, 90=perpendicular, clamps)\n- **Azimuth**: Direction of tilt (0-360 degrees, wraps)\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- Prelude\n- Schema.Bounded\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[97,29],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Tilt/Atoms.purs","start":[97,15]},"title":"TiltX"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Brush","Tilt","Atoms"],"TiltX"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[99,36],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Tilt/Atoms.purs","start":[99,1]},"title":"eqTiltX"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Ord"],"Ord"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Brush","Tilt","Atoms"],"TiltX"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[100,38],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Tilt/Atoms.purs","start":[100,1]},"title":"ordTiltX"},{"comments":null,"